library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
## 
## Attaching package: 'tidyr'
## The following object is masked from 'package:magrittr':
## 
##     extract
library(readr)

class_dat = read.delim("C:/Users/Lena Kan/Desktop/PFRH/2019-2020/Term 3/Full Credit Classes/Public Health and Data Science/assignments/assignment 3/data/classInterests.txt", sep= "", colClasses = c("Year" = "character", "Program" = "character")) 

year_plot <- ggplot(data = class_dat, aes(x= Year), ylab= "Frequency")+
  geom_bar(stat= "count", fill= "steelblue")+
  theme_minimal()+
  ggtitle("Year Barplot")+
  labs(y = "Frequency")+ 
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 25), text = element_text(size=20), axis.text.x = element_text(size=14), axis.text.y = element_text(size=14))

program_plot <- ggplot(data = class_dat, aes(x= Program), ylab= "Frequency")+
  geom_bar(stat= "count", fill= "steelblue")+
  theme_minimal()+
  ggtitle("Program Barplot")+
  labs(y = "Frequency")+ 
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 25), text = element_text(size=20), axis.text.x = element_text(size=14), axis.text.y = element_text(size=14))

library(ggplot2)
library(ggmosaic)
library(RColorBrewer)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(readr)


mosaic_plot = ggplot(class_dat) + geom_mosaic(aes(x=product(Program, Year), fill=Program, na.rm=TRUE)) + labs(x="Year", y = "Program", title = "Class Program vs. Year", position = "identity") +theme(text = element_text(size=12),
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle=70, hjust=1)) + theme(axis.text.y =  element_text(vjust = 0.1, size=10,colour="black")) + scale_fill_brewer(palette="Spectral")

Part 4: Gene expression data (demeaning)

library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(readr)

gene_data <- read.csv("C:/Users/Lena Kan/Desktop/PFRH/2019-2020/Term 3/Full Credit Classes/Public Health and Data Science/assignments/assignment 3/data/GSE5859_exprs.csv", header=TRUE)

gene_data_2 <- select(gene_data, -X)
row_mean <- rowMeans(gene_data_2)
sweep = sweep(gene_data_2, 1, row_mean)
col_mean <- colMeans(gene_data_2)
finalsweep = sweep(sweep, 2, col_mean)

finalsweep[1:10, 1:5] #check if final sweep works

#Alternative: for loop

row = rowMeans(gene_data_2)
col = colMeans(gene_data_2)
row_matrix = matrix(row, ncol=1, nrow=8793)
col_matrix= matrix(col, ncol = 208, nrow = 1)

demeaned_matrix = matrix(,ncol = 208, nrow = 8793)
for(i in 1:8793){
  for(j in 1:208){
    demeaned_matrix[i,j] = gene_data_2[i,j] - row_matrix[i,1] - col_matrix[1,j]
  }
}

colnames(demeaned_matrix) = colnames(gene_data_2)
demeaned_matrix[1:10, 1:5] #matches the sweep function

Part 5: Healthcare spending data

library(readr)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyverse)
## -- Attaching packages ---------------------------------------------------- tidyverse 1.3.0 --
## v tibble  2.1.3     v stringr 1.4.0
## v purrr   0.3.3     v forcats 0.4.0
## -- Conflicts ------------------------------------------------------- tidyverse_conflicts() --
## x tidyr::extract()   masks magrittr::extract()
## x dplyr::filter()    masks stats::filter()
## x dplyr::lag()       masks stats::lag()
## x purrr::set_names() masks magrittr::set_names()
healthcare_spending <- read.csv("C:/Users/Lena Kan/Desktop/PFRH/2019-2020/Term 3/Full Credit Classes/Public Health and Data Science/assignments/assignment 3/data/healthcare-spending.csv")
long_healthcare <- healthcare_spending %>% 
  gather(Year, Total.Health.Spending, "X1991__Total.Health.Spending":"X2014__Total.Health.Spending")
long_healthcare = select(long_healthcare, -X)

long_healthcare$Year = substr(long_healthcare$Year, 2,5)
long_healthcare$Total.Health.Spending = long_healthcare$Total.Health.Spending/ 1000

long_healthcare = filter(long_healthcare, Location != "United States")

state_spending_plot = ggplot(data = long_healthcare, aes (x=Year, y = long_healthcare$Total.Health.Spending))+
  geom_point(aes(x= Year, y = Total.Health.Spending, colour = Location))+
  labs(title="Healthcare spending by state", x="Year", y="Total Healthcare Spending in 1000's ($)")+
  theme(text = element_text(size=12),
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle=70, hjust=1))+
  theme(legend.text = element_text(colour="blue", size=12, face="bold"))+
  labs(colour = "State")+
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 300, 10))


state_spending_plot

Part 6: Barplot of average state healthcare spending

library(tidyr)
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)

avg_cost_state = long_healthcare %>% 
  group_by(Location) %>% 
  summarise(mean(Total.Health.Spending))

average_spending_plot = ggplot(data= avg_cost_state, aes(x=Location, y= avg_cost_state$`mean(Total.Health.Spending)`))+
  geom_bar(stat= "identity", fill = "steelblue")+
  theme(text = element_text(size=20),
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle=70, hjust=1))+
  labs(x = "State", y = "Average cost in 1000's ($)", title = "Average cost per state")

average_spending_plot
